Data Settings for Dashboard Line Chart Components

Line charts are useful for showing data over time.
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs)
Available in: Group (View Only), Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

NEEDED
To create dashboards: Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you created: Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you created in public folders: Edit My Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you didnâ€™t create in public folders: Manage Dashboards in Public Folders

For example, to see the numbers of leads created each month in a report, set record count as the Y-axis and created month for the X-axis.

SETTING	DESCRIPTION
Y-Axis	Choose what values to display on the vertical axis of your bar, column, scatter, or line chart.
X-Axis	Choose what values to display on the horizontal axis of your bar, column, scatter, or line chart.
Group By	Choose how to group information on your chart.
Combination Chart	Select this option to plot additional values on this chart.
Display Units	Choose a scale for displaying your chart values.
Drill Down to	Select where users go when they click a dashboard component.
title: Configuring Line Charts in Salesforce Dashboards
